ocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vfq1665702655924.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vfq1665702655924.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vfq1665702655924.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"exercise dita\" id=\"vfq1665702655924\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determine whether to compile components, application shells, and global ProcScripts\n      that can be debugged,</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__topic_d142097e1_d142098e1_d142099e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__p_d142100e1_d142101e1_d142102e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NO_DEBUG</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">0</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__section_vfg_xz5_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d561338e68\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__table_d17036e1_d17037e1_d17038e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">0 </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__section_gb4_11v_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d561338e116\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__p_d142109e1_d142110e1_d142111e1\">When <code class=\"ph codeph\">$NO_DEBUG = 1</code>, compiling\n            components, application shells, and global ProcScripts generates corresponding runtime\n            objects that cannot be debugged. This is useful when preparing an application for\n            release. It is the equivalent of using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/nodebug</span> command line\n            switch.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vfq1665702655924__note_hgx_35t_qwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">DebugPort</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">EnableDevTools</span> properties are ignored or disabled in case a\n            component is compiled with /nodebug.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrz1665702655781.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/nodebug</a><p>Instruct Uniface to compile the application shell, component, or global ProcScript so that it cannot be debugged.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616494\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616494\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$NO_DEBUG Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 01, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determine whether to compile components, application shells, and global ProcScripts that can be debugged, $NO_DEBUG { = } 1 | 0 Defaults Assignment file: ide.asn Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: 0 Description When $NO_DEBUG = 1 , compiling components, application shells, and global ProcScripts generates corresponding runtime objects that cannot be debugged. This is useful when preparing an application for release. It is the equivalent of using the /nodebug command line switch. Note: The DebugPort and EnableDevTools properties are ignored or disabled in case a component is compiled with /nodebug. Related Links /nodebug Instruct Uniface to compile the application shell, component, or global ProcScript so that it cannot be debugged. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}